Business Brief -- Analog Devices Inc.:
   Sales Drop Seen Resulting
   In Nominal Profit or Loss
Jerald Fishman, president and chief operating officer,
said: "The major disappointment in the quarter was the
shortfall in bookings, which adversely affected shipments.
Bookings began to rise in mid-fourth quarter and continued
improving through most of December." He said that orders for
the fiscal first quarter will be about $133 million, down
from $138.2 million in the year-ago period.